                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-597" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES TINSLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to Mr. Dewey. This is his bridle—it was taken from the stable about the 10th or 12th of September, and found on one of Mr. Giddens's horses.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370130-name-598" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-598" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-598" type="surname" value="GIDDENS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-598" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS GIDDENS</persName>
                  </hi>. This bridle was found on one of my horse—I bought it of the prisoner, about the 14th of September, for 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he said a man had been up to Barnet fair with a horse, and gave him the bridle, and said he would not take it home with him—I live at South Mimms—I knew he lived with the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>
